Class Overview

Information describing a turn in a set of navigation instructions.

Navigation directions are communicated as a "turn event" where the driver sees information describing their next required action (turn, merge, etc.) to arrive at the destination.

public int getTurnAngle ()

Gets the angle at which the driver should exit the roundabout relative to their entrance.

Example: In a roundabout with four, evenly spaced exits, the first exit is getTurnAngle()=90; the second exit is getTurnAngle()=180; the third exit is getTurnAngle()=270. The angle is counted in the direction of travel around the roundabout (clockwise for roads where the car drives on the left side of the road, such as Australia; counter-clockwise for roads where the car drives on the right side of the road, such as the USA).

Returns
int The angle in degrees. A value of 0 means this is unset.

public int getTurnNumber ()

Gets the roundabout exit number that the driver should use to exit the roundabout relative to their entrance.

Example: In a roundabout with four, evenly spaced exits, the first exit is getTurnNumber()=1; the second exit is getTurnNumber()=2; the third exit is getTurnNumber()=3. The exit is counted in the direction of travel around the roundabout (clockwise for roads where the car drives on the left side of the road, such as Australia; counter-clockwise for roads where the car drives on the right side of the road, such as the USA).

Returns
int The exit number. A value of 0 means this is unset.

protected void readFromBundle (Bundle bundle)

Reads the states saved in the Bundle into the current instance. The implementation should mirror that of #writeToBundle(Bundle).

Parameters

protected void writeToBundle (Bundle bundle)

Writes the states of the instance to the given Bundle. Only primitives or system classes can be written into the Bundle. If a field of a custom class needs to be serialized, serialize it into a new Bundle and then write that Bundle into the outer Bundle. A list or array of custom class instances should similarly be converted into an array of Bundles first.

Parameters
bundle Bundle
